Which Intel processor type should you recommend for an HP MultiSeat host PC that
supports six to ten access devices, each running high-processing-demand applications
such as multimedia?
A. Core 2 Duo
B. Core 2 Quad
C. Core i7
D. Xeon processor 5600 series
Answer: D

A. Intel Xeon based host PC

C. licensing support through Microsoft Volume Licensing
D. support for up to 24 access devices
E. support for access devices running Windows 7 only
Answer: B,E
